      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's not resting though. there is no waking up. there's nothing left to wake up to. it's just been years of pretending, of dragging this empty body through the motions because i'm \"supposed\" to. but honestly? it feels like a mistake. like i'm just an occupant in a space that should have been vacant a long time ago. it's exhausting to keep being a ghost when you're still tethered to the earth.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
